I always intended to go to university, and my parents were keen that I went to university, but I don\rquote 
t think I got any particular encouragement from school.  In fact, some of the subjects I did well at were subjects I asked to do exams on, which they did not have teachers for.  One was Classics and I taught myself, basically, for that.  So those were the
 things that were interesting me, that got me into anthropology, I suppose. Ancient history and Classics.
