mbling in the corridor that to be interested in urban anthropology is a waste of time.  And so that was very much the atmosphere that surrounded urban type stuff.  But the Manchester Group was different on that.  It wasn\rquote 
t that they were doing urban and ru
ral stuff, it was because of their overall system position, which came from their influence from Marxist kinds of positions. Their argument was that the urban and the rural were not separate, but were articulations within a sin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
