 I first arrived in Central Africa, I think his first wife had just died from cancer, and he was very retiring at that point.  But he was extremely warm, and in contrast to Max, really didn\rquote t wish to impose his personality on somebody else\rquote }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7940072 s work.  He was really Socratic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10699196\charrsid10699196 
 in his method, in that he would elicit from you what you thought, rather than impose his opinion.  So it was a tremendous. He used to make his students feel they were really going places.  He was a wonder}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
