 work, but it was in a sense, to some extent, it was a bit like an extension of Max. But that was fine.  He was a huge intellect.  I think Cl
yde and Jaap van Volsen, and Vic Turner, and Ian Cunnison were in awe of Max.  I mean, Max had - he was this big tall guy, and he had, it seemed, to us, an eidetic memory.  He had a capacity to absorb fieldwork and material at a great depth, and an abilit
y
